The death toll from a powerful earthquake in China has exceeded 12,000 in Sichuan province alone, the official Xinhua news agency reported on Tuesday, quoting the local government.
Nearly 26,000 people are still buried in earthquake debris and another 14,000 are missing after the massive earthquake that struck China's Sichuan province.
There had been no minor quakes in the area around the epicenter of the 7.8-magnitude earthquake in southwest China's Sichuan Province before the strong earthquake took place on May 12.
